SQL Database Application
•	Connect Java to a SQLite database (module7.db).
•	Demonstrates SQL queries, insertion, deletion, and retrieval inside a Java application.
•	Main class: SQL.java
•	Database file: module7.db

Requirements
•	Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 or higher
•	IntelliJ IDEA (Community or Ultimate Edition)
•	SQLite JDBC driver (sqlite-jdbc-x.x.x.jar) added to project libraries

Running in IntelliJ IDEA
1.	Open IntelliJ IDEA.
o	Go to File > New > Project from Existing Sources...
o	Select the folder containing these .java files.
2.	Configure JDK.
o	Choose Java SDK 17 or higher.
3.	Add SQLite JDBC dependency.
o	Download the sqlite-jdbc JAR file.
o	In IntelliJ, go to File > Project Structure > Libraries > Add JAR/Directory and attach it.
4.	Run the desired application.
o	Open one of the main files (MechanicApp.java, PasswordValidationApp.java, DivisionApp.java, BattleApp.java, Anime.java, DemoApp.java, or SQL.java).
o	Right-click → Run 'ClassName.main()'.

